ÏRÁQ<?php exit; ?>a:1:{s:7:"content";O:8:"stdClass":24:{s:2:"ID";i:4831;s:11:"post_author";s:1:"1";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2013-04-20 13:54:22";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2013-04-20 21:54:22";s:12:"post_content";s:694:"These are the Yellow games.

Yellow games are paused campaigns, or campaigns waiting for the "green" light to become Green games.

This means the game publisher is testing the conversions and is generally not paying for conversions yet (but in some cases, they do pay).

Do not wait for a game to go Green! Use the "zzz" Play Now links.

Why?

Because this helps convince game publishers to create a budget and start paying for conversions in more countries!

See this answer in video:
<a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=cUwPpAfwSNM&list=PLyI74zGGymu8k7eVhGPcVSh3nKljHfiVX#t=1m33s">http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=cUwPpAfwSNM&list=PLyI74zGGymu8k7eVhGPcVSh3nKljHfiVX#t=1m33s</a>";s:10:"post_title";s:21:"What are "zzz" games?";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:4:"open";s:11:"ping_status";s:4:"open";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:9:"zzz-games";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2013-04-20 14:02:30";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2013-04-20 22:02:30";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";i:0;s:4:"guid";s:50:"http://www.any.tv/?post_type=avada_faq&#038;p=4831";s:10:"menu_order";i:20;s:9:"post_type";s:9:"avada_faq";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"0";s:6:"filter";s:3:"raw";}}